rComments: Professor Sauer is designed a create class this past fall. The class had 2 midterms (20% each) and a final (48%) and weekly online quizzes that make up the rest of the marks. The midterms were relatively easy, and the final was non- cumulative (only 4 lectures). If you keep up with weekly quizzes, you can attain a grade of 80% or above.

She is very understanding and tries to get people to come to lectures. Her explanations are clear and she uses relevant videos to further elaborate on the content. Her exam was fair and it was not necessary to read the textbook; lectures were enough. She has a sense of humour.

She is an awesome prof, not going to lie but beware the final exam is tough!! Midterms were so easy, class average was so high but then came along the final. Lecture based, but gotta do some research on the topics yourself if you want to be prepared for the application questions.
